# Testing (Vitest)

## Where tests live

- Unit: `apps/admin/src/__tests__/unit/**/*.test.ts`
- Integration: `apps/admin/src/__tests__/integration/**/*.test.ts`
- Helpers: `apps/admin/src/__tests__/helpers/`
- Run with `npm test --workspace=apps/admin` (or `npm run test:coverage`).

## Integration tests — the DB pattern

Integration tests use an in-memory SQLite created by `createTestDb()`. **Mock `@/lib/db` with `vi.mock` before importing the route under test** — never call `getDb()` directly in test setup.

```typescript
import { describe, it, expect, vi, beforeEach } from 'vitest'
import { NextRequest } from 'next/server'
import { createTestDb } from '../helpers/db'
import type Database from 'better-sqlite3'

let testDb: Database.Database

vi.mock('@/lib/db', () => ({
  getDb: () => testDb,
  getSetting: vi.fn().mockReturnValue(null),
}))

vi.mock('@/lib/email', () => ({
  sendEmailConfirmation: vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(undefined),
  // ...mock every email helper used by the route
}))

const { POST } = await import('@/app/api/posts/route')

beforeEach(() => { testDb = createTestDb() })
```

## Building requests

Build `NextRequest` directly with JSON body and an `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header. Generate tokens via `generateToken({ sub, email, role })` from `@/lib/auth`.

## Coverage targets

| Area | Minimum line coverage |
|---|---|
| Auth & RBAC | 90% |
| New utility modules | 80% |

## Required test cases for new API routes

At minimum, cover: success (`2xx`), `401` (no/invalid token), `403` (RBAC denial), input validation (`400`), and any sanitization invariants (e.g., XSS stripped from stored content).
